British doctors in Scotland studied telomere length in middle-aged men to identify those at high risk of heart disease.
Statin treatment reduced heart disease risk for men with short telomeres.
A gene variant in women increases the likelihood of coronary artery disease.
Periodontal disease may also be linked to pancreatic cancer.
Stress in childhood can impact inflammation levels, increasing the risk of heart disease in adulthood.
Air pollution is a significant risk factor for cardiovascular disease, especially for postmenopausal women.
Research emphasizes the importance of early detection and personalized medicine in reducing heart disease risk.
